stylometry: Optimization is coming up with the best answer to optimize the objective function.  This can either be to minimize something or to maximize something.  The compenents of a linear programming model are decision variables, target cells, input variables.  The decision variables are the cells in which we put information that we fits in the problem into our spreadsheet.  THe input variables is what we put into the spreadsheet that is given to us in the problem.  The target cells are the cells in which we want to change and either maximize or minimize to come up with the answer to our problem.
